To Gerald:<br>
     I agree with you.  Regardless of my feelings on the wall, it has given many of our brother vets the healing they deserve and need.  For that, it is worth its weight in gold.  It gives us, the vet, recognition and healing and that is the best point about it.  It wouldn't matter what it looked like, and its too late to worry about that now.  All that matters now is that America not forget the sacrifice and service of its Nam vets.    
